   I know where all of this nonsense about my lady started. Dorka is the cause of all of this, because she hid the death of the servant and acted as if she was still alive. And it would not have been necessary to secretly bury the two German maids on Lady Kata's wedding day if we had informed our lady of the accident. The discovery of the corpses brought misfortune down upon this house. It is too late to clear any of this up. Dorka and the rest are dead and nobody will believe me. It is all left in the hands of God..."
